    #4                   Not Infallible!
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This canary scheme is not infallible. Although signing the declaration
makes it very difficult for a third party to produce arbitrary
declarations, it does not prevent them from using force or other
means, like blackmail or compromising the signers' laptops, to coerce
us to produce false declarations.

Keep a lookout for other strange red flags, such as:


   [ ] disappearance of previously existing warrant canaries;

   [ ] unexplained closing or deletion of public repositories;

   [ ] not responding to direct inquiries regarding warrants
       or gag orders; or

   [ ] if the format of this canary changes considerably without
       explanation and no longer includes definitive statements
       regarding requests.


Any of these red flags should give cause to discontinue use of taskhive
for your own security until your requests can be answered.

